TITLE: Rishi Sunak will become the next U.K. prime minister
SUMMARY: A popular former chancellor of the exchequer under Boris Johnson's premiership, Sunak lost out to Liz Truss in the race to replace him earlier this summer.

TITLE: A Washington state woman fended off a black bear attack
SUMMARY: The woman sustained non-life threatening injuries and is being treated at a hospital, according to officials. Wildlife officers killed a bear found nearby.

TITLE: Children's hospitals grapple with a nationwide surge in RSV infections
SUMMARY: The latest spike is months early and it's pushing care facilities to capacity. Children under the age of 5 are most vulnerable.

TITLE: The first Nation's Report Card since COVID shows math and reading scores are down
SUMMARY: The test measures reading and math proficiency for fourth- and eighth-graders. It's administered every two years, but the pandemic delayed the 2021 report until now.

TITLE: Jury selection begins in the Trump Organization tax evasion trial
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump's family company has long been involved in countless business disputes that landed it in civil court. But it has never been tried in a court of law for crimes, until now.

TITLE: Democrats are losing Latino voters as Republicans eye opportunities these midterms
SUMMARY: While Democratic strategists acknowledge past mistakes and make renewed pledges to woo Latino voters, Republicans are also making inroads.

TITLE: The U.S. set a new record for apprehensions at the southern border
SUMMARY: Migrants apprehensions at the southern border this past year jumped by 37% compared to the year ago. A growing number of border-crossers are from Venezuela, Cuba and Nicaragua.

TITLE: As a new trial starts, here's where the cases concerning George Floyd's murder stand
SUMMARY: A jury trial is set to begin in Minnesota court for former officers Tou Thao and J. Alexander Kueng, who pleaded not guilty to charges of aiding and abetting the murder and manslaughter of Floyd.

TITLE: Those fake active shooter calls to schools? A similar thing happened before
SUMMARY: As schools across the U.S. are targeted by false calls about active shooters, NPR has found evidence that a similar scheme took place in the spring.

TITLE: Residents across India celebrate Diwali with festivities and dazzling lights
SUMMARY: Indians celebrated Diwali on Monday as bright oil lamps and colorful lights lit up homes and streets across the country to mark the Hindu festival that symbolizes the victory of light over darkness.

TITLE: The Houston Astros and Philadelphia Phillies will face each other in the World Series
SUMMARY: Major League Baseball has its World Series lineup cards set, as the Houston Astros will face the Philadelphia Phillies.

TITLE: Deaths from southern tribal clashes in Sudan reach at least 220
SUMMARY: Two days of tribal fighting in Sudan's south killed at least 220 people, a senior health official said Sunday, marking one the deadliest bouts of tribal violence in recent years.

TITLE: Boris Johnson drops out of the race to be the next U.K. prime minister
SUMMARY: Treasury chief Rishi Sunak is now the strong favorite to become Britain's next prime minister — the third this year — at a time of political turmoil and severe economic challenges.

TITLE: N.Y. officials announce plans for a memorial to the victims of the Buffalo shooting
SUMMARY: The May 14th Memorial Commission is a step in the state's long-term commitment to supporting and uplifting the East Side Buffalo community, officials say.

TITLE: Woodward's taped time with Trump reveals much about both the author and his subject
SUMMARY: We hear the former president striving to court Woodward's favor, praising him as "a great historian" and "the great Bob Woodward." Yet these interviews veer often into disagreements and even debates.
